Policy 1: ADMIN_TO_ATTACKER
Purpose:
Allows Admin LAN VM to communicate with the Attacker VM for testing, pings, file 
transfers, and firewall visibility.
Key Configuration:
• Incoming: ADMIN_LAN (port2)
• Outgoing: ATTACKER (port3)
• Source: Admin-Subnet
• Destination: Attacker-Subnet
• Service: ALL
• Action: ACCEPT
• NAT: Enabled
Why NAT is ON?
Even for internal traffic, FortiGate may require NAT depending on routing. This prevents 
asymmetric routing issues.
What logs are generated?
• Forward traffic logs (connection start/close)
• Application logs (if App Control enabled)
• IPS logs (if attack traffic is detected)
• Web filter logs (if attacker hosts web services
